image.altText: An older man standing in front of a long shop window.

props.synopsis: Hardware store owner Frank Penhalluriack faced massive fines, financial ruin and went to jail as he fought for what he believed in. He won, and has changed how we live, work and socialise.

title.children: Frank thought you should be able to do jobs around the house on weekends. It put him in jail

image.altText: Queen Margrethe wears a crown and ornate necklace with sash over her blue gown while seated for portrait

props.synopsis: After more than 50 years on the throne, Denmark's Queen Margrethe is abdicating to her son. But there was one man who could never come as close to the queen as her crown.

title.children: Queen Margrethe's husband brutally turned on her. But during his funeral, he made one final gesture of love

image.altText: The back of a woman standing in front of a moving blurry train

props.synopsis: This modern-day mystery has been reported for decades, and one expert studying the phenomenon believes he might know what causes the strange pulsating sound only some can hear.

title.children: The curious hum that only some people around the world seem to be able to hear

image.altText: People hold protest signs with messages like 'Bridget must go' and 'Don't say 3-way'.

props.synopsis: Christian and Bridget Ziegler had been rising stars of the Florida Republicans, promoting conservative family values. Then came revelations of a threesome with a woman, who alleges she was later raped by Mr Ziegler.

title.children: A Florida power couple promoted the 'Don't Say Gay' law. Then came revelations of a threesome and an alleged assault

image.altText: A woman in a gold formal dress splashes into the sunny ocean.

props.synopsis: Every year these pleasure-seeking Australians take to the waves in suits and ball gowns to let off steam during the summer holiday silly season.

title.children: 'Like being washed in happiness': The formal-wear beach swim shoring up pleasure

image.altText: A large crowd of people pushing each other.

props.synopsis: Multiple videos circulating on social media appear to show a brawl at Summernats involving dozens of men, some of whom are wearing "crowd safety" vests.

title.children: Police investigating brawl at Summernats with footage showing some involved wearing 'crowd safety' vests

image.altText: About 10 police officers talk near a car at a large crime scene on a suburban street.

props.synopsis: Police say a man fatally shot in Donnybrook on Melbourne's northern fringe was part of a group of armed intruders who seriously assaulted one of the residents moments before the shooting.

title.children: A man shot dead on a suburban street in Melbourne's outer north was an armed intruder, police say

image.altText: A police officer stands near a police car at night.

props.synopsis: Police believe a string of stabbing attacks across Melbourne that left multiple people in hospital was random, with no connection between the accused and the victims.

title.children: Man charged over string of Melbourne stabbings which left multiple people in hospital

image.altText: A close up of a smiling Nigel Lythgoe at a red carpet event

props.synopsis: Nigel Lythgoe, who is also a co-creator and executive producer of the show, said he is dedicating his time to "clearing my name" following three separate sexual assault lawsuits.

title.children: So You Think You Can Dance judge Lythgoe steps down amid several sexual assault allegations

image.altText: Australia batter David Warner touches his baggy green cap while smiling.

props.synopsis: David Warner's Test career was prolific, exciting and unique. Now that it's over, properly assessing his standing in the pantheon of Australian cricket is a challenge, writes Jon Healy.

title.children: David Warner is Australia's most prolific Test opener, but there's one major caveat around his status as a great of the game

image.altText: A hole in the side of a plane

props.synopsis: The Boeing model is grounded in the US after Alaska Airline pilots were forced to make an emergency landing when a blowout caused a gaping hole in the side of the plane.

title.children: Some Boeing 737-9 Max jetliners return to air after Alaska Airlines blowout

image.altText: Ale de Minaur hits a double-fisted backhand at the United Cup.

props.synopsis: For the first time in 18 years, Australia will have a player ranked inside the men's top 10, with Alex de Minaur tipped to be a threat at the season-opening major in Melbourne.

title.children: Gone are the 'shaky' forehand and the 'weak' second serve, as de Minaur cracks the top 10

image.altText: A composite image of a a man, a woman with blonde hair and a woman with black hair.

props.synopsis: After scandals, boycotts and a complete overhaul, the Golden Globes are back to kick-off the 2024 awards season.

title.children: Golden Globe Awards 2024: How to watch, who's hosting and why this year will be a test for the future

image.altText: Cars submerged by floodwaters in Cairns.

props.synopsis: When the Bureau of Meteorology declared an El Niño, there were warnings of a hot and dry summer. But for thousands of Australians, that's not been the case at all. Why not?

title.children: Isn't it meant to be El Niño? Here's why it hasn't been the hot, dry summer we expected

image.altText: A cloud of smoke billows through the sky as a rocket takes off

props.synopsis: The spacecraft has reached its home for the next five years, an orbit from where it will study the Sun and its influence on space weather.

title.children: India's Aditya-L1 spacecraft reaches Sun orbit

image.altText: A drag queen wearing a rainbow tshirt sits and applied concealer in the mirror.

props.synopsis: When Kymm Apostolides was a teenager and living in a small regional town, he was administered electric aversion therapy when he began wearing his sister's clothes. Fifty years later, he's a vital part of the mid-north community.

title.children: From conversion therapy to community acceptance: Taking drag to rural Australia for a good cause

image.altText: A young boy practicing judo.

props.synopsis: James Gittus's family says the suit means the Tasmanian state judo champion can compete and train without an increased risk of injury as well as go to school full time.

title.children: NDIS says 'no' to funding state judo champion's special suit he needs to compete

image.altText: A group of cyclists sitting on their bikes looking solemn, one cyclist comforts another with an arm around the other.

props.synopsis: Competitors at the three-day AusCycling Road National Championships in Ballarat have taken a moment of silence in honour of the renowned Olympian, who died on Saturday, December 30.

title.children: 'Amazing athlete': Cyclists pay touching tribute to beloved champion Melissa Hoskins

image.altText: A young woman wearing hiking gear stands in a misty field amongst small tents.

props.synopsis: At 21 years old, Cleo Darke is older than many of the young men who fought and died on the Kokoda Track during World War II. It's something she thought about often as she retraced their steps.

title.children: In the wild jungles of Papua New Guinea, 21-year-old Cleo finally found peace

image.altText: Angourie Rice sits in math class in a still from 2024's Mean Girls.

props.synopsis: Angourie Rice has a much-loved and much-watched DVD of the 2004 film version of Mean Girls, now she plays a starring role in its latest adaptation.

title.children: Angourie grew up watching iconic American high school films. Now, she's in one

image.altText: A painted portrait of a man with longer dark hair.

props.synopsis: A team of archaeologists discovered the remains of the 16th-century father of modern astronomy, who was the first to demonstrate that the Earth orbits the Sun.

title.children: Copernicus's grave was lost for centuries. An unlikely discovery finally solved the mystery

image.altText: A woman using a phone.

props.synopsis: Hitting the dating apps today, but hesitating because of a previous negative experience? App companies say don't be deterred, but do stand up for yourself when swiping right.

title.children: Today is 'Dating Sunday' so if you're looking for love online, there are ways to protect yourself

image.altText: image of baby flying fox held in a wrap with a dummy in it's mouth

props.synopsis: Wildlife carers say grey-headed flying foxes are "amazing creatures" — but the species is dying at an alarming rate, and they're running out of volunteers to help save them.

title.children: Wildlife care groups forced to euthanase abandoned flying fox pups amid shortage of volunteers to care for them

image.altText: Katrina screams in delight as she celebrates on the field.

props.synopsis: As she prepares to link up with Matildas teammate Mackenzie Arnold, Katrina Gorry says she is relishing the challenge of joining the Women's Super League after signing with West Ham United.

title.children: Globetrotting Matilda 'grateful' to land at West Ham

image.altText: Socceroos players celebrate a goal against Bahrain.

props.synopsis: A hard-fought and frustrating 2-0 friendly win over Bahrain is the "perfect" tune-up for the Socceroos' Asian Cup campaign, according to coach Graham Arnold.

title.children: Socceroos beat Bahrain in final Asian Cup warm-up

image.altText: cute puppy running towards the camera

props.synopsis: Canberra's RSPCA shelter is caring for more than double its usual number of animals.

title.children: This animal shelter is bursting at the seams with ferrets, galahs, kittens and puppies

image.altText: Six women standing with their bikes before going on a ride.

props.synopsis: Nancy Wake famously rode about 500 kilometres in 72 hours, bluffing her way through Gestapo checkpoints to transmit a message. These riders will take a more leisurely approach to honour the war hero.

title.children: Veteran women to honour war hero Nancy Wake with ride through France

image.altText: Storm cells range with lightning thunder before a golden sunset glow

props.synopsis: Authorities say heavy rainfall is expected to arrive in the Victoria's north-west from Sunday night and move across the state, with residents warned to plan for flash flooding.

title.children: Storms, flash flooding likely in Victoria from today, with up to 200mm of rain possible in state's north

image.altText: A sign saying "The Royal Children's Hospital" sits in a garden in front of one of the facility's large, colourful buildings.

props.synopsis: A mother in her 20s is understood to have avoided contact with medical services throughout her pregnancy, but sought hospital assistance on the day of her baby's birth.

title.children: Newborn in critical condition after 'freebirth' in regional Victoria

image.altText: Aryna Sabalenka fist pumping.

props.synopsis: Tennis fans will get an early taste of what the Australian Open final could be when Aryna Sabalenka and Elena Rybakina face off in the Brisbane International final.

title.children: Sabalenka sets up Australian Open final rematch with Rybakina in Brisbane

image.altText: Smoke rises from village.

props.synopsis: Lebanon's Hezbollah militia fires dozens of rockets at northern Israel on Saturday as top US and EU diplomats visit the region to seek ways to halt spillover from the war.

title.children: Hezbollah says it hit Israeli observation post with 62 rockets
